rComments: she seems frightening, but she's actually very approachable - gives really fair tests, and explains the course material very clearly. also the class was super interesting!
I didn't understand her at times but I found her lectures interesting. I didn't like my TA in the lab and I found the text and the lectures contradicted themselves sometimes.

Her course is a joke. Didn't put any effort at all and still ended up with 4.0 GPA with her. Tutorials are plain useless. Some students find it hard because of the TAs. I don't know if she has a marking scheme or not, but the TAs are very bias. You'll end up with A if you had a good TA, but it's hard to get A if you had a bad TA.
Hard tests, kinda rude, but okay prof. Answers questions when you ask them.
Okay class. Two hour lectures were sometimes snooze-worthy. Check over your lab tests VERY carefully... marking errors do happen!

Wasn't a bad prof & was very helpful at the small study sessions she held (where she went over the midterm and effective study skills). I got a B+ with minimal effort/cramming for 2 hours before the exam (don't try this!). Class average was a C+. Exam was a repeat of case studies/exact questions from past exams. Emphasis on concepts, not details.

Reads from her notes a lot, but then again, she has really good notes. Posts them online. The online bio quizzes are freebie marks, make sure you don't miss any. Her tests are pretty fair as well.

Lectures are kind of useless as she posts the slides online. I personally haven't approached her but my friends got no help. She make quizzes unnecessarily tricky. Tutorials are plain useless. I very rarely read the textbook and managed an A. My advice: memorize her lecture notes. Exam was semi-easy.

I asked her a question from the textbook once and she didn't know how to arrive to the answer either so she just flipped to the answers and told me it...SHES NOT HELPFUL! She puts me asleep too, I've skipped someof her classes and still managed A-. The material isn't that hard because its more about general concepts then facts you have to memorize.

the worst prof in first year sciences - its not a wonder shes not on tenure and is only a sessional instructor... dont listen to what she says, it will confuse you for bio 153, dont go to her "tutorials" unless you wanna laugh at her math - just get her lecture notes and read the textbook. the most useless woman in the school. course was easy tho.

the course was a joke. honestly, don't even go to her lecs, all of the notes are posted online...very disorganized, but they're there...i did little to no work, and i got 94%

In 152, was an excellent professor. Clearly outlined important facts and made lectures interesting. 206 was a DISASTER! Lectures rarely reflected exam material, lectures were often rushed and she confused what she was trying to say. Don't understand what happened.

also had her in BIO152...she was ok back then compared to the other prof...but in BIO206 she was ridiculous....the tests weren't fair....the assignments kill when most of the students in the class are handling 3 bio courses at the same time....and goin to her classes were a waste of time cuz they were so disorganized....
for BIO152 she was great, fair tests and all that, for BIO206...argh what happened? I don't know you'd have to ask her.
reviews a lot and gives fair tests. concepts aren't difficult but don't underestimate difficulty on tests, especially at 8am in the morning.

She is very clear and helpful. Her tests are easy to predict, because she covers everything necessary in class. She should teach all of BIO152 instead of Anderson!

Brutally repetitive. I could have sworn the first 10 slides of every single lecture in the bio 152 course were identical...wasting an unnecessary half an hour of the limited one hour session we have. Despite this aspect that makes her class very redundant, she does have passion, and is a fair prof.
really easy tests
she does her job very well! she tests only on the material that she mentions, you won't see any concepts/questions on the test/exam that she has never discussed!
